On Tue, Dec 23, 2003 at 05:20:04PM +0100, Sven Luther wrote:

> Mmm, not really convinced. For me ;, is a shortcut for :
> 
>   let () = ... in
> 
> Actually, i believe that both constructs result in the exact same code.

